CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1958, pg. A6 reads: "Congratulations! - The Iota Chapter of AKA Sorority placed second in the annual Greek Week Sing at the University of Pittsburgh recently. in the competition were about 30 other sororities and fraternities on the campus. Left to right, seated, are Marva Jones, Andrea Jones and Louella Blow.  Standing: Lee Bertha West, Stephanie Johnson, Helen Adair, Francis Ruffin and Mrs. Nan Currington, graduate adviser. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Kappa Alpha sorority second place winners of Greek Week Sing, seated from left: Marva Jones, Andrea Jones, Louella Blow; standing: Lee Bertha West, Stephanie Johnson, Helen Adair holding trophy, Francis Ruffin, and Nan Moone Currington, posed in interior with swirl patterned carpet
